title: Märklin H0 - 3327 - Electric locomotive Series BR 1100 of the NS
description: Märklin H0 - 3327 - Electric locomotive Series BR 1100 of the NSCompany Number-1135Loc has been digitalisedAddress 78 Locomotive number: Track 1135 In the Blue/Yellow NS Livery No damage or paint issues Tested on functionsHet model is een 1100 Company Number-1135 in blauw/gele uitvoering van de Nederlandse Spoorwegen (NS) uit tijdperk IV. Het model is Analoog en is in het bezit van een 3-polige Drum Collector Motor (DCM). De 3327 heeft een 3-punts verlichting welke wisselt met de rijrichting. History: The 60 locomotives of the series 1100 were built in France by Alsthom in the 1950's and 60's. They had a max speed of 135 km/h, on continuous output of 1900kW. The locomotives of series 1100 were used for goods and passenger trains. Since 1978 the remaining 58 locomotives were fitted with a centre buffer and a strengthened cabin forepeak, (botsneus) which would provide the engineer with more safety. The walkway and the sound proofing in the cabin were also adjusted. The model 3324 by Märklin is an analogue version of loco 1139 of the Netherlands Railways. The model has the blunt nose and is in yellow-grey livery.See the photos for a clear impression of the item
